The [[Yochlol]]s [[Yiccardaria]] and [[Eskavidne]] initially summoned the driders who would come to form the bulk of the Blaspheme from the [[Demonweb Pits]] in the {{YearlinkName|1488}} as an army to gift to Matron [[Zhindia Melarn]]<ref>{{cite book/Relentless|99-100}} so as to foment chaos among the drow of Menzoberranzan,<ref>{{cite book/Relentless|426}} making it look like Zhindia enjoyed the favor of Lolth in greater proportion than any other of the city's matrons, while also tipping the balance of temporal power in the city in her house's favor.<ref>{{cite book/Relentless|111}}
When Zhindia's forces were about to clash with those of [[House Baenre]] and its allies on the surface, a magical trap had been set up, empowered by the [[birth magic]] sent out by [[Catti-brie]] during the birth of [[Briennelle Zaharina|her daughter]].<ref>{{cite book/Relentless|417}} When any drider stepped through this trap, they were painfully transformed back into humanoid drow.<ref>{{cite book/Relentless|423}} Seeing the opportunity after the first transformations, all of the other driders present on the battlefield, from both armies, willingly entered the trap, transforming themselves back into their original drow forms.<ref>{{cite book/Relentless|425}} After the battle swiftly concluded, the identities of the newly-transformed drow were recorded and all armies returned home, taking the former driders with them.{{cite book/Relentless|438}}

Once in Menzoberranzan, the former driders began fighting against the Lolthites in the city, in a conflict expected to take years, if not decades to resolve.
